{
  "texts": [
    "Notably, the ALBERT model diverges from BERT in its training approach.",
    "Instead of utilizing the next sentence prediction (NSP) task employed by BERT, the ALBERT model employs the Sentence Order Prediction (SOP) task.The NSP task in BERT comprises a binary classification task, where positive samples are generated by extracting two consecutive sentences from the same document, while negative samples entail sentences from different documents.",
    "This task primarily aims to enhance downstream task performance.",
    "However, the NSP task, in essence, encapsulates two subtasks: topic prediction and relationship consistency prediction.",
    "Notably, topic prediction is relatively straightforward, focusing on discerning differences in topics between two sentences."
  ]
}